<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-06-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="172" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                    <head>No. 168.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Phelps</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-06-01"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 1,
                            1886</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 310.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my instructions No. 289, of
                        the 11th ultimo, and No. 303, of the same month, transmitting to you for
                        your information copies of my recent notes to Sir Lionel West concerning the
                        fisheries question, I now inclose herewith for your further information two
                        copies of a note which I addressed on the 20th ultimo to Her Britannic
                        Majesty’s minister at this capital in relation to house of commons bill No.
                        136, now pending in the Dominion Parliament, entitled “An act further to
                        amend the act respecting fishing by foreign vessels.”</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed></closer>
                    <frus:attachment>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg></opener>
                        <dateline>[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1886-05-29">May 29,
                            1886</date>]</dateline>
                        <p>Mr. Bayard to Sir L. West, May 29, 1886. For Inclosure see No. 187, <ref target="#pg_380">p. 380</ref>.</p>
                    </frus:attachment>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>